---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { COMPANY } from '../consts';

const lastUpdated = '23 April 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Play Inspection Software"
  description="Privacy policy for playinspectionsoftware.co.uk — how we collect, use, and protect your information under UK GDPR."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-slate mt-10 max-w-none prose-headings:font-semibold prose-headings:text-slate-900 prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline">
      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        This website (<strong>playinspectionsoftware.co.uk</strong>) is operated by
        <strong>Michael Stevenson</strong>, trading as <strong>Autaimate</strong>
        (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;, &ldquo;our&rdquo;).
      </p>
      <p>
        We are the data controller responsible for any personal information
        processed through this website under the UK General Data Protection
        Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Contact for data protection enquiries:</strong><br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:mick@autaimate.com">mick@autaimate.com</a><br />
        Post: 45 Vicarage Road, St Austell, Cornwall, PL24 2PH, United Kingdom
      </p>

      <h2>2. What information we collect</h2>
      <p>
        We keep data collection to the minimum necessary to operate this website.
        The information we process falls into two categories:
      </p>
      <h3>2.1 Information you provide</h3>
      <p>
        If you email us (for example, to request a demo), we receive the email
        address you send from along with the contents of your message. We do not
        operate contact forms on this website at present.
      </p>
      <h3>2.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Server logs</strong> — our hosting provider, Cloudflare,
          records technical information about each request (IP address, browser
          user-agent, requested URL, timestamp) for security and abuse-prevention
          purposes. These logs are retained by Cloudflare for a limited period
          and are not used for marketing.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — we use Cloudflare&rsquo;s
          privacy-first analytics service to measure aggregate traffic (page
          views, referring sites, country-level location). This service uses no
          cookies, does not fingerprint visitors, and does not collect personal
          information. For this reason it is exempt from PECR cookie consent
          requirements.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we use your information</h2>
      <p>We use the information described above only to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to enquiries you send us;</li>
        <li>Maintain the security and availability of the website;</li>
        <li>
          Understand aggregate usage patterns so we can improve the content and
          performance of the website.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell, rent, or trade personal information. We do not use
        personal information for profiling or automated decision-making.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Legal basis for processing</h2>
      <p>Under UK GDPR, we rely on the following lawful bases:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> (Article 6(1)(f)) — for server
          logs, security monitoring, and privacy-friendly aggregate analytics.
          Our legitimate interest is operating a secure, functional website.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Consent</strong> (Article 6(1)(a)) — where you voluntarily
          contact us by email, you consent to us using that information to
          respond.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Third parties</h2>
      <p>
        We share personal information only with service providers strictly
        necessary to operate the website:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare, Inc.</strong> — hosting, content delivery network,
          DDoS protection, and privacy-first analytics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Google LLC</strong> — we have registered the website with
          Google Search Console, which provides aggregate data about how the
          site appears in Google search results. No personal visitor data is
          shared with Google by us.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Some of these providers are based outside the United Kingdom. Where data
        is transferred internationally, we rely on appropriate safeguards such
        as the UK International Data Transfer Agreement or the UK Extension to
        the EU-US Data Privacy Framework.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain email correspondence for as long as is necessary to handle
        your enquiry and for a reasonable period afterwards in case of
        follow-up. Server logs and aggregate analytics are retained according to
        Cloudflare&rsquo;s own retention schedules.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your rights under UK GDPR</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to the personal information we hold about you;</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate personal information;</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your personal information;</li>
        <li>Object to or restrict our processing of your information;</li>
        <li>Request a portable copy of information you have provided to us;</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time, where consent is the legal basis.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, email
        <a href="mailto:mick@autaimate.com">mick@autaimate.com</a>. We will respond within
        one calendar month.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are unhappy with how we have handled your personal information,
        you have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner&rsquo;s
        Office (ICO): <a href="https://ico.org.uk" rel="noopener" target="_blank">ico.org.uk</a>,
        0303 123 1113.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This website does not set any cookies of its own. Cloudflare may set
        strictly necessary cookies for security purposes (for example, to detect
        and block malicious traffic). These are exempt from consent requirements
        under the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations (PECR) as
        they are essential for the service to function.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Security</h2>
      <p>
        This website enforces HTTPS connections with TLS 1.2 or higher,
        HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS), and a Content Security Policy.
        Data in transit between your browser and our servers is encrypted.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be
        reflected on this page with a revised &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Email
        <a href="mailto:mick@autaimate.com">mick@autaimate.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
